      "span_text": "The Pb(II)-EDTA 2-complex shows a reduction potential in the interval -0.5 to -0.6 V vs. the Ag/ AgCl reference electrode, which is considerably more negative than that of Tl(I), which in turn does not form EDTA complexes, so it maintains its peak at the same potential (-0.44 V), effectively removing the interference of Pb(II) illustrated in the previous section (Fig. 2a)."
